ReportQuery.SQLStatement:
select 'Yesterday' as Interval, z.ReportDate, z.UserName, z.TargetAF_MQty_AbsError, z.TargetAF_MQty_Error, z.FeedingScheduleMixGID as 'LoadNo', z.CompanyName from IngredientMix z where z.ReportDate = convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))
union all
select 'LastWeek', z.ReportDate, z.UserName, z.TargetAF_MQty_AbsError, z.TargetAF_MQty_Error, z.FeedingScheduleMixGID as 'LoadNo', z.CompanyName from IngredientMix z where DATEPART(YEAR, z.ReportDate) = case when DATEPART(WEEK, convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))) = 1 then DATEPART(year, convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))) - 1 else DATEPART(year, convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))) end and DATEPART(week, z.ReportDate) = case when datepart(week, convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))) = 1 then 52 else DATEPART(week, convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))) - 1 end
union all
select 'CurMonth', z.ReportDate, z.UserName, z.TargetAF_MQty_AbsError, z.TargetAF_MQty_Error, z.FeedingScheduleMixGID as 'LoadNo', z.CompanyName from IngredientMix z where DATEPART(year, z.ReportDate) = case when DATEPART(month, convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))) = 1 then DATEPART(year, convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))) - 1 else DATEPART(year, convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))) end and DATEPART(month, z.ReportDate) = case when DATEPART(month, convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))) = 1 then 12 else DATEPART(month, convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))) end and z.ReportDate <= convert(date, dateadd(day, -1, GetDate()))
